handgrip_condition.Description: Participant's experiment condition for the IHG task

Levels.Control: Participants do not squeeze the ball during the blue cue
Levels.IHG: Participants squeeze the ball during the blue cue

hormone_group.Description: Participant's hormone group. Note that LU and HC are younger adult women and PM are older adult women

Levels.LU: Luteal group - subjects in the luteal phase of their menstrual cycle
Levels.HC: Hormonal contraceptive group - subjects taking hormonal contraceptive

T1w.json.Title: T1 Anatomical Image
T1w.json.Description: This is a high-resolution anatomical scan of the brain

task-IHG_bold.json.Description: Subjects focused on luminance-normed visual cues that prompted them when to squeeze/grip without squeezing (HG/CTRL) and rest.

Event.Description: The specific task event that occurs at this onset timestamp

Levels.Rest: Subjects are resting without gripping the ball
Levels.Grip: Subjects are gripping the ball either without squeezing (Control group) or squeezing with maximal force (Handgrip group)

Cue.Description: The visual cue that appears on the screen the prompts subjects to grip or rest

Levels.Yellow: Rest - subjects relax without gripping the ball
Levels.Blue: Grip - subjects grip the ball without squeezing (Control) or squeezing with maximal force (Handgrip)

task-Oddball_bold.json.Description: Participants heard either high-pitch (Oddball), low-pitch (Standard), or natural (Novel) tones. Participants were instructed to respond by button press to Oddball tones only.

TrialEvent.Description: The specific trial event that occurs at this onset timestamp

Levels.TrialStart: Marks the onset of the trial start
Levels.ToneStart: Marks the onset of the 200-ms tone

ToneLabel.Description: The type of 200-ms tone clip played in this trial

Levels.Novel: Natural novel tone (participants should not respond)

CRESP.Description: The correct response for this trial

RESP.Description: The participant's response to this trial

ACC.Description: The participant's response accuracy for this trial (i.e., ACC = 1 if RESP == CRESP)

RT.Description: Response time to the tone (if button was pressed)

Code.Description: Trial response code (based on CRESP and RESP)

Levels.Hit: Correctly responded to Oddball tone (CRESP = 1, RESP = 1)
Levels.FalseAlarm: Incorrectly responded to non-Oddball tone (CRESP = 0, RESP = 1)

README:
OpenNeuro curator note: This dataset was previously accessible at ds002572. The dataset was reuploaded due to privacy considerations. 

The behavioral, functional and structural MRI data found in this repository have been published in:

Mather, M., Huang, R., Clewett, D.V., Nielsen, S., Velasco, R., Tu, K., Han, S., & Kennedy, B.L. (2020). Isometric exercise facilitates attention to salient events in women via the noradrenergic system. NeuroImage 210:116560

Additional pupillometry, behavioral, and subject data related to this project can be found in this OSF repository: https://osf.io/2y47s/?view_only=ff3af10779cb42a8a5b0e26620f81d4f.

Subject folders are labeled by their experiment id (e.g., "sub-101, sub-201, sub-301"). Subjects in the 100 series are LU (luteal phase younger women); 200 series are HC (hormonal contraceptive younger women); and 300 series are PM (post-menopausal older women).

Contained within the anat and func sub-folders for each subject are the following acquisitions (with a few exceptions described below):
1) anat (2 acquisitions) - T1-weighted anatomical image, T1 FSE (neuromelanin-weighted) image of the pontine brainstem slices

2) func (2 to 3 acquisitions) - Isometric Handgrip functional scan, Oddball task functional task (run 1), Oddball task functional scan (run 2, if acquired)

Notes:
After our first set of participants, data collection protocol was modified so that only one run of the oddball task was administered. The published study uses only oddball run 1; however, data from both runs (if available) are provided in the respository.
In participants.tsv, the "exclude" column tags subjects who were excluded from neuroimaging analyses in the published study. We recommend using the same exclusions when analyzing this dataset.

BIDS warnings:
Code 25 EVENTS_TSV_MISSING - Behavioral data missing for sub-101 (pilot participant) because some experiment programs were modified after piloting
Code 38 INCONSISTENT_SUBJECTS - Oddball run 2 acquisition files are missing for subjects who only did one run of the task
Code 39 INCONSISTENT_PARAMETERS - These 3 acquisitions were acquired during "pilot" before our scan sequences were modified. Thus, the inconsistency in dimensions.
